<H2>Cannabis Through the Ages</H2>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="13" CELLSPACING="0">

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2">
<B>ca.<BR>440<BR>B.C.</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2">
<A HREF="scynth.tpl"><B>Herodotus</B></A><BR>
This brief description of Scythian purification rites is one of the earliest known descriptions of marijuana use.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1705</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="loyal.tpl">
<B>The Loyalist Post</B></A><BR>
A list of arguments published in order to encourage English colonists to grow hemp.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1766</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="abstrac.tpl"><B>Abstract from a Treatise on Hemp</B></A><BR>
An effort to encourage Colonial Americans to grow hemp, it describes recreational, industrial and medical uses along with some interesting historical background.</font></TD>
</TR>
<TR>

<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1815</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2">
<A HREF="tjeff.tpl"><B>Jefferson's Hemp Break</B></A><BR>
Thomas Jefferson provides a good argument for hemp cultivation in a letter which describes his idea for a device for breaking hemp - a most difficult but necessary step in preparing hemp stalks for fiber production.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1860</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="divine1860.tpl"><B>The Divine Weed</B></A><BR>
Speculation's and theories about exactly when the practice of smoking marijuana was introduced to the United States and the writings of the late 1850s that had a tremendous impact on the American people.
</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1883</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="hashhou.tpl"><B>A Hashish-House in New York</B></A><BR>
The curious adventures of an individual who indulged in a few pipefuls of the narcotic hemp.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1895</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2">
<A HREF="orgy.tpl"><B>Orgies of the Hemp Eaters</B></A><BR> This article from the long-defunct New York Herald newspaper describes the exotic rituals of the Nosairiyeh tribesmen of northern Syria, whose ceremonies involved consuming vast quantities of hashish. </font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1902</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="ushemp1902.tpl"><B>The American Hemp Industry</B></A><BR> A very early account summarizing the American hemp industry as it existed near the turn of the 20th century.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1917</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="decorti.tpl"><B>The Decorticating Machine</B></A><BR> George Schlichten perfected a machine which revolutionized the processing of hemp ... and then both he and his machine disappeared from the pages of history.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1920</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="modernhemp1920.tpl"><B>Revolutionizing an Industry</B></A><BR> 
Published article on the progress and inventors who devoted their most able energies toward the perfection of mechanical devices that would take the backache out of hemp breaking and revolutionize the industry.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1926</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="homehas.tpl"><B>Science and Invention: Our Home Hasheesh Crop</B></A><BR>
The opinion of government plant-scientists given in response to an inquiry from Science Service.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1937</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="youthas.tpl"><B>Marijuana: Assassin of Youth</B></A><BR>
Harry J. Anslinger's alarmist study of adolescent cannabis use.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1938</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"> <A HREF="moredangerous1938.tpl"><B>Marihuana More Dangerous Than Heroin or Cocaine</B></A><BR>
A short article in the May 1938 issue of Scientific American that is probably the most extreme and bizarre example of Harry Anslinger's "Reefer Madness" campaign.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1995</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/Magazine/1995/9509/aroundw.tpl"><B>Hemp Around the
World</B></A><BR>
From China to Canada to Chile, tall, green hemp plants are being converted into dozens of environmentally friendly products.</font></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>1996</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/Magazine/1996/9604/hinhome.tpl"><B>Hemp in the Home</B></A><BR>
A guide to all the products you can use to hempify your home.</font></TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFE23D" VALIGN="TOP">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><B>&nbsp;</B></font></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#D9DBC0">
<font face="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="/Magazine/1996/9604/busihem.tpl"><B>The Business of Hemp</B></A><BR>
Some of the world's leading authorities on hemp talk about where the hemp industry is, where it's going and how it's going to get there.</font></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

